01:20.680 --> 01:24.378
<i>♪ I just haven't met you yet ♪</i>

01:24.651 --> 01:27.120
( HUMMING)

01:31.691 --> 01:35.492
<i>♪ I might have to wait</i>
<i>I'll never give up ♪</i>

01:35.562 --> 01:39.556
<i>♪ I guess it's half timing</i>
<i>and the other half's luck ♪</i>

01:39.632 --> 01:43.262
<i>♪ Wherever you are</i>
<i>whenever it's right ♪</i>

01:43.336 --> 01:47.296
<i>♪ You'll come out of nowhere</i>
<i>and into my life ♪</i>

01:47.373 --> 01:51.367
<i>♪ I know that we can be</i>
<i>so amazing ♪</i>

01:51.444 --> 01:54.505
<i>♪ And maybe love is gonna</i>
<i>change me ♪</i>

01:54.581 --> 01:57.199
Wait for me! Hey!

01:57.283 --> 01:58.774
Hey, wait for me!

01:58.852 --> 02:00.377
Hey! Get ba...

02:00.453 --> 02:04.618
<i>♪ And somehow I know that it</i>
<i>will all turn out♪</i>

02:04.691 --> 02:08.856
<i>♪ You'll make me work</i>
<i>so we can work to work it out ♪</i>

02:08.928 --> 02:11.796
<i>♪ And a promise you keep ♪</i>

02:11.865 --> 02:14.300
<i>♪ I give so much more than I...</i>

02:14.367 --> 02:18.270
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

02:42.362 --> 02:46.231
<i>(MUSIC FADES UP)</i>

03:05.952 --> 03:09.286
<i>(MUSIC CONTINUES)</i>

03:35.982 --> 03:37.610
Hi, Daisy!

03:37.684 --> 03:38.879
Hi, Sam.

03:38.952 --> 03:42.548
Uh, you doing... stuff?

03:42.622 --> 03:45.956
I was thinking of flying
over to the glow worm trail.

03:46.025 --> 03:48.620
You want to go? Who, me?

03:48.695 --> 03:50.687
Yes, I would... like to go...

03:50.763 --> 03:53.562
to the trail... with you,
there, please?

03:54.400 --> 03:57.234
Looks like someone
has a girlfriend.

03:57.303 --> 04:00.364
I bet you they'll love
and care for each other.

04:00.440 --> 04:01.440
Oh, gross.

04:01.507 --> 04:03.669
Oh, man, put some cork
in a twitch.

04:03.743 --> 04:07.339
Ooh... smoochy, smoochy.

04:08.281 --> 04:10.773
Max! Agh! Both of you!

04:10.850 --> 04:13.820
Daisy, sorry, just ignore them.

04:13.886 --> 04:15.684
Later then,
at the glow worm trail?

04:15.755 --> 04:18.748
Sounds great, Sam.
I'll meet you there!

04:19.492 --> 04:21.892
Fantastic! I'll...
I'll see you soon!

04:24.797 --> 04:26.288
I can't believe you two!

04:26.366 --> 04:28.858
That's pretty much the most
I've said to Daisy ever!

04:28.935 --> 04:30.927
Now we're on a date.

04:31.004 --> 04:33.701
Can't you two just leave me
alone for two minutes?

04:33.773 --> 04:36.868
You're always just tagging
along beside me.

04:47.053 --> 04:48.453
Hey, Sammy, wait up!

04:48.521 --> 04:50.581
Agh, just leave me alone,
William.

04:50.657 --> 04:51.784
I want to talk to you.

04:51.858 --> 04:52.985
Forget it.

04:53.059 --> 04:56.518
You might have been a little harsh
with Max and Twitch back there.

04:56.596 --> 04:58.292
(SIGHS)

04:58.364 --> 04:59.855
They started it.

04:59.932 --> 05:02.527
They just can't leave me alone,
even for a minute.

05:02.602 --> 05:04.036
They're your best friends, bro.

05:04.103 --> 05:07.596
If they say stuff that you don't like,
you can't let it get under your wings.

05:07.674 --> 05:11.304
Sometimes others don't understand
that when they joke around...

05:11.377 --> 05:13.471
it can actually hurt feelings.

05:13.546 --> 05:16.573
Look, just keep your chin up,
and always take the high flight.

05:16.649 --> 05:17.708
Okay.

05:17.784 --> 05:21.380
They're your friends, just treat
them how you want to be treated.

05:24.090 --> 05:25.615
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

05:25.692 --> 05:28.856
You! You vile giant!

05:28.928 --> 05:33.957
You think you can come into our world,
destroy the natural beauty surrounding us?

05:34.033 --> 05:38.095
No, sir! Not today!
Not on my watch!

05:45.978 --> 05:47.970
[KING] Die, human scum!

05:48.047 --> 05:50.107
No, please! Take the king, not...

05:50.383 --> 05:52.648
Oh, sir... it's you.

05:52.719 --> 05:54.711
Huh? What is it?

05:54.787 --> 05:56.779
Your sons, my king...

05:56.856 --> 05:58.882
they are late for their fitting.

05:59.625 --> 06:00.854
Go! Get 'em!

06:00.927 --> 06:02.555
Yes, sir!

06:05.665 --> 06:08.464
Agh! I don't really want
to do this, but...

06:08.534 --> 06:11.026
I can't be late again.
Dad'll kill me.

06:11.104 --> 06:13.403
Sorry, Nature.

06:16.976 --> 06:18.035
(GASPS)

06:20.580 --> 06:22.879
William! Sam!

06:22.949 --> 06:24.417
Fly!

06:25.718 --> 06:27.414
Sammy!

06:27.487 --> 06:28.487
William!

06:31.524 --> 06:33.516
William!

06:37.764 --> 06:40.131
William? Sammy?

06:42.869 --> 06:46.169
Sam, oh, am I glad to see you.

06:46.439 --> 06:48.032
Your father would have
had my head if...

06:48.107 --> 06:49.107
(GASPS)

06:50.910 --> 06:53.141
Will? Sam, you don't want to...

06:53.212 --> 06:56.478
Will? Will, wake up.

06:59.085 --> 07:03.546
Well, he's alive... but barely.

07:03.623 --> 07:06.149
William needs
medical attention, now!

07:06.225 --> 07:08.490
Take him to the infirmary!

07:13.199 --> 07:15.862
Samuel... my son...

07:15.935 --> 07:19.929
now is not a time for tears.

07:20.006 --> 07:24.501
For eons, we Pixies
have been a proud community...

07:24.577 --> 07:27.672
and so it has been
for generations...

07:27.747 --> 07:33.015
whomsoever performs a misdeed against us,
suffers the fate of the Pixie Curse.

07:34.020 --> 07:40.483
Samuel, my son, you shall bear the
brunt of our curse against this enemy.

07:40.560 --> 07:45.589
Take that human back home and insure
that he lives a life of misfortune...

07:45.665 --> 07:51.468
for all of eternity,
so say I, king of the Pixies!

07:57.176 --> 07:59.145
Don't worry, we'll get him.

07:59.212 --> 08:01.977
For sure... we'll get him.

08:02.048 --> 08:04.517
We'll get him good.

08:06.285 --> 08:09.084
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i> (SIGHS)

08:09.155 --> 08:10.817
Long day.

08:16.963 --> 08:20.092
Ahh... honey, I'm home.

08:20.166 --> 08:24.194
Hm, looks like it's just me
and you again, bed.

08:30.543 --> 08:31.806
(SNORING)

08:35.047 --> 08:37.607
That guy can really sleep.

08:37.683 --> 08:40.517
Talk about hittin' the snooze
button, huh?

08:40.586 --> 08:42.145
Where's Sam?

08:42.221 --> 08:44.656
Getting ice cream? You wish.

08:44.724 --> 08:48.092
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

08:52.598 --> 08:54.123
About time.

08:54.200 --> 08:55.691
Hello to you, too.

08:55.768 --> 08:57.896
Max, Twitch...

08:57.970 --> 09:00.701
to insure victory in combat,
you must study your opponent.

09:00.773 --> 09:04.210
Admire, respect their
attributes.

09:04.277 --> 09:07.076
Now, let's drop a book
on his face.

09:08.948 --> 09:12.180
Ow! Stupid shelf.

09:14.921 --> 09:16.321
Oh!

09:16.589 --> 09:19.582
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

09:19.659 --> 09:21.287
(YAWNING)

09:29.702 --> 09:32.968
Yow! Ow!

09:42.348 --> 09:44.613
( LAUGHING)

09:44.684 --> 09:48.712
Oh, man, great work, guys...
seriously.

09:48.788 --> 09:51.781
Oh, we've only just begun.

09:54.226 --> 09:57.663
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

10:07.039 --> 10:08.769
(CHUCKLES)

10:08.841 --> 10:10.104
(SNIFFING)

10:10.176 --> 10:11.337
Ahh.

10:12.945 --> 10:14.038
Yeah.

10:19.085 --> 10:21.350
Hmm. Mm-mm?

10:22.922 --> 10:26.620
Don't remember opening that
thing, hmm. Oh, well.

10:29.862 --> 10:33.264
<i>(MUSIC CONTINUES)</i>

10:33.332 --> 10:36.359
(VACUUM RUNNING)

11:08.000 --> 11:09.730
Agh! Oh, no!

11:09.802 --> 11:11.737
Fire! Fire! Fire!

11:22.848 --> 11:25.909
<i>(MUSIC CONTINUES)</i>

11:30.389 --> 11:31.413
Hmm.

11:31.490 --> 11:33.186
Agh!

11:35.127 --> 11:37.687
You okay? Yeah, I'm good.

11:41.467 --> 11:43.766
Oop, get that.

11:46.772 --> 11:47.831
( MUMBLES INDISTINCT)

11:47.907 --> 11:49.432
Huh?

11:49.508 --> 11:51.340
Cat head. Did you say something?

11:52.845 --> 11:54.370
Joe, you okay? I'm good.

11:55.247 --> 11:56.943
Hmm.

11:59.418 --> 12:02.911
<i>(MUSIC CONTINUES)</i>

12:04.857 --> 12:06.917
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

12:28.280 --> 12:30.078
Yeah, yeah!

12:37.356 --> 12:40.019
Agh! My foot!

12:41.827 --> 12:44.888
<i>(MUSIC CHANGES)</i>

12:46.532 --> 12:50.162
For the umpteenth time,
I'm not going out with you, Joe.

12:50.236 --> 12:52.398
Aw, come on, Betty,
it'll be great!

12:52.471 --> 12:54.940
We could play doctor.

12:55.007 --> 12:58.000
No, my work and home lives
are separate, thank you.

12:58.077 --> 12:59.978
But we already know
each other so well.

13:00.045 --> 13:02.537
And that's why I have to turn
a charmer like you down.

13:02.815 --> 13:05.375
Last thing I need to date
is a walking disaster.

13:05.451 --> 13:07.147
Ouch.

13:07.219 --> 13:08.551
You're a nice guy, Joe...

13:08.821 --> 13:12.917
but you'll be a lot nicer when I don't
see you here three times a week.

13:12.992 --> 13:15.325
That was colder
than your stethoscope.

13:17.530 --> 13:19.021
Whoa! Whoa!

13:21.200 --> 13:24.432
Go on, get out of here.
Scoot, scoot.

13:24.503 --> 13:26.335
All right. Git!

13:28.974 --> 13:30.101
( BRAKES SQUEALING)

13:30.176 --> 13:32.304
(CAR HORN HONKING)
Whoa, yeah, my bad.

13:32.545 --> 13:34.070
[JOE] Sorry.

13:36.515 --> 13:39.508
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

13:42.488 --> 13:46.584
Something's wrong, my luck
these days is just horrible.

13:49.461 --> 13:50.827
Huh?

13:52.231 --> 13:53.597
Huh?

14:07.613 --> 14:09.935
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

14:10.015 --> 14:11.015
Hello?

14:11.050 --> 14:13.042
Joe, where the heck are you?

14:13.118 --> 14:16.555
I'm on my way, sorry,
I had an accident.

14:16.622 --> 14:18.989
Again with the accidents.

14:19.058 --> 14:22.551
Ma'am, just bring your keys to Vincent over
there and he'll take good care of you.

14:22.628 --> 14:25.530
Vincent? You put Vincent
in the shop?

14:25.598 --> 14:27.123
What? He's good.

14:27.199 --> 14:29.430
He doesn't know his alternator
from his elbow.

14:29.501 --> 14:32.994
Maybe, but his elbow is on time.

14:33.072 --> 14:36.975
You said you'd be done in an
hour. One hour, you said!

14:37.042 --> 14:38.340
We'll miss the special!

14:38.410 --> 14:40.606
How is she supposed
to get her blintzes?

14:40.679 --> 14:43.080
I love the blintzes.

14:44.350 --> 14:47.047
She loves the blintzes,
crazy about 'em!

14:47.119 --> 14:49.054
All she has left
are these blintzes!

14:49.121 --> 14:50.987
And now... no blintzes.

14:51.056 --> 14:53.321
I don't know what to do
without blintzes.

14:53.392 --> 14:55.361
She is lost without these
blintzes.

14:55.427 --> 14:57.453
You're tearing her apart here,
I tell you!

14:57.529 --> 14:59.521
Apart is what we're torn!

14:59.598 --> 15:01.362
Something bad will happen.

15:01.433 --> 15:04.028
She needs the blintzes!

15:04.103 --> 15:06.572
Joe, just...
just get here quickly.

15:06.639 --> 15:08.267
We need you at the desk.

15:08.340 --> 15:12.175
Dad, I can work on the...
the cars, Dad!

15:12.244 --> 15:13.610
I'm actually very competent.

15:13.679 --> 15:16.079
It's not like every second of
my life is a complete disast...

15:17.249 --> 15:18.683
Whoa.

15:18.951 --> 15:19.975
You guys do that one?

15:20.052 --> 15:21.987
That one was all
the wingless wonder.

15:22.054 --> 15:23.420
(ALL LAUGHING)

15:25.524 --> 15:28.494
Agh! Just one moment of peace!

15:30.429 --> 15:32.557
Oh, my gosh, are you okay?

15:32.631 --> 15:35.499
I'm fine, just fine, I...

15:35.567 --> 15:37.661
<i>(HARP MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

15:37.736 --> 15:40.706
Are you sure? Because I hit you
pretty hard with that door.

15:40.973 --> 15:45.035
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

15:45.110 --> 15:47.011
Aw, that looks pretty bad.

15:47.079 --> 15:48.274
Uh...

15:48.347 --> 15:49.975
You know, I wasn't even
paying attention.

15:50.049 --> 15:52.177
I was just fiddling around
with my phone thing.

15:52.251 --> 15:56.382
Technological distraction, just more
industrial junk to distract us, right?

15:56.455 --> 15:58.185
Ooh, kitty video!

15:58.257 --> 16:00.351
<i>(KITTY MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

16:05.464 --> 16:07.330
Guy... hey! Snap out of it.

16:07.399 --> 16:09.959
Come on, let's go
get you some ice.

16:10.035 --> 16:13.164
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

16:19.311 --> 16:21.143
Take a load off.

16:23.148 --> 16:25.481
Oh, relax, I'll be right
back with that ice.

16:25.551 --> 16:27.452
Welcome to the jungle, baby.

16:31.557 --> 16:34.026
Oh, wow, she's so cute.

16:34.093 --> 16:35.618
Maybe my luck has changed.

16:35.694 --> 16:37.560
(SINK RUNNING)

16:37.629 --> 16:43.068
<i>JOE (V.O.) Um, I should
say something. Uh...</i>

16:43.135 --> 16:45.036
You take all these?

16:45.104 --> 16:47.369
Yup! Each and every one.

16:47.439 --> 16:48.702
This is the Valdez spill?

16:48.774 --> 16:51.734
[MICHELLE] Yeah, I took that one when
I was seven, just before my birthday.

16:51.744 --> 16:52.643
Where's this?

16:52.711 --> 16:54.111
[GIRL] Which one?

16:54.179 --> 16:55.704
The kid on a pile of tech junk.

16:55.781 --> 16:58.410
[GIRL] Oh, India...

16:58.484 --> 17:00.749
You know most of our tech waste ends
up in a landfill in foreign countries?

17:00.819 --> 17:03.015
Eh, didn't know.

17:03.088 --> 17:06.684
[GIRL]
Uh, I might be out of ice.

17:06.759 --> 17:09.126
Hey, this tsunami one
is pretty intense.

17:09.194 --> 17:10.719
[GIRL] Yeah, Sumatra...

17:10.755 --> 17:13.396
I was having some freshly roasted
coffee with a few travel mates...

17:13.398 --> 17:14.731
when, whoosh! It just hit!

17:14.800 --> 17:16.769
I mean, lucky timing, I guess.

17:16.835 --> 17:18.701
Hey, I can't find any ice,
but I got this.

17:18.771 --> 17:20.501
Got what? Here.

17:22.540 --> 17:24.601
Do you always attack
your guests with meat products?

17:24.675 --> 17:28.477
Um, it's Tofurky,
so technically it's not meat.

17:28.547 --> 17:30.311
And I don't have ice,
so this is gonna have to do.

17:30.382 --> 17:34.251
Avegan with a throwing arm, I
didn't think that was possible.

17:34.319 --> 17:36.618
Hey, if you have a problem with vegans,
you're gonna have two black eyes.

17:36.688 --> 17:39.749
No, no, this is good.
I surrender.

17:41.460 --> 17:44.430
Atta boy, we vegans aren't
all that bad, are we?

17:44.496 --> 17:47.830
I guess not. Pictures
are a little heavy, though.

17:48.100 --> 17:52.128
Negative effects of environmental abuse
was a good angle for my last art show.

17:52.204 --> 17:54.639
I'm actually getting ready
for my next art show this week.

17:54.706 --> 17:58.336
It's a diorama set of a 1950's amusement
park, and I've sculpted everything...

17:58.410 --> 17:59.469
Hear anything?

17:59.545 --> 18:03.482
I think I discovered a secret,
human language.

18:03.549 --> 18:09.546
( MUTTERING GIBBERISH )

18:11.657 --> 18:13.523
Hey, guys, check this out.

18:13.592 --> 18:16.562
Looks like Joe might
have a girlfriend.

18:16.628 --> 18:18.790
We'll see about that.

18:21.700 --> 18:23.532
I'd like to hear
what they're saying.

18:23.602 --> 18:26.572
You can see it on his face.
He's...

18:26.638 --> 18:27.867
In love.

18:28.140 --> 18:30.132
Isn't that how you
look at Daisy?

18:30.209 --> 18:31.438
No! I don't!

18:31.510 --> 18:34.503
You do! You <i>so</i> do.

18:34.580 --> 18:37.277
Okay, dead wings for both
of you.

18:38.517 --> 18:41.510
This sculpture is incredible.
You're very talented.

18:41.587 --> 18:43.215
Well, thank you,
thank you very much.

18:43.288 --> 18:46.850
World traveler, masterful
artist, Elvis impersonator...

18:46.925 --> 18:49.292
and a looker to boot.

18:49.361 --> 18:52.798
You probably'd say that to all the
people who physically assault you.

18:52.865 --> 18:54.356
No, I'm serious.

18:54.433 --> 18:56.299
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

18:57.936 --> 19:02.738
Uh, hey, Dad, no, I...
I had another...

19:02.808 --> 19:06.438
Yeah, yeah, I know, but I...

19:06.512 --> 19:08.242
I'll be right there.

19:08.313 --> 19:10.578
Hear anything?

19:10.649 --> 19:13.813
I can't hear a thing
but my conscience crying.

19:13.886 --> 19:14.910
What?

19:15.187 --> 19:16.917
I mean, maybe we should
take a break.

19:17.189 --> 19:20.921
And get lectured by your dad?
No, thanks!

19:21.193 --> 19:24.254
I could go for some eats. There's
a Mexican skip around here.

19:24.329 --> 19:27.595
It's supposed to be
<i>muy deliciosa!</i>

19:27.666 --> 19:30.192
Is that on your Wing Watchers
approved diet?

19:30.269 --> 19:35.173
No, but in the city, no one can
hear me eating burritos.

19:35.240 --> 19:37.903
It's actually your silent ones
that are the problem.

19:37.976 --> 19:40.673
You are so dead!

19:40.746 --> 19:43.773
I'd rather take my dad's
lecture.

19:43.849 --> 19:46.341
Listen, I'm running late
for work.

19:46.418 --> 19:48.785
Oh, my gosh, I'm sorry
to have kept you.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.880
No, no, the pleasure
is all mine.

19:50.956 --> 19:54.256
I, uh... I was wondering...

19:54.326 --> 19:57.455
If I treat you to an apology
dinner for smashing your face?

19:57.529 --> 19:59.828
Uh, yeah? Yeah.

19:59.898 --> 20:01.196
Sure.

20:01.266 --> 20:02.666
For real?

20:02.734 --> 20:04.225
My name is Michelle.

20:04.303 --> 20:07.296
Joe... nice to have my face
smashed by you.

20:07.372 --> 20:09.603
Pleasure was all mine.

20:09.675 --> 20:12.702
This is the part where
you ask for my number.

20:12.778 --> 20:15.907
I'm... I'm not very good
at this, am I?

20:15.981 --> 20:18.849
No, Joe, you're not.

20:22.421 --> 20:25.516
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

20:28.427 --> 20:30.453
Max, did you just power bomb
Twitch?

20:30.529 --> 20:36.400
<i>Yo quiero nacho libre!</i>
<i>El Supremo Maximo!</i>

20:36.468 --> 20:38.403
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

20:38.470 --> 20:39.768
Oh, yeah!

20:42.374 --> 20:44.502
Who da' man? You da' man.

20:44.576 --> 20:49.537
Whoa, that's a lady.
You da' lady, man.

20:51.016 --> 20:53.008
Sammy, our mark is leaving.

20:56.922 --> 21:01.257
Guys! Come on! Let's give
it a rest for a bit.

21:02.628 --> 21:06.395
<i>(MUSIC CONTINUES)</i>

21:08.634 --> 21:10.660
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

21:14.306 --> 21:15.399
Yeah.

21:17.743 --> 21:20.679
She likes me!
She really likes m...

21:24.549 --> 21:27.849
[JOE] Hey, Dad, I'm
gonna be a little late.

21:27.919 --> 21:30.582
( LAUGHING)

21:31.723 --> 21:33.419
You guys are impossible.

21:33.492 --> 21:36.519
<i>(MUSIC CONTINUES)</i>

22:10.028 --> 22:12.554
Hey! Today ruled!

22:12.631 --> 22:14.964
Michelle's the greatest thing
I've ever seen.

22:16.935 --> 22:20.770
Doo, doo, doo, dah, doo...

22:33.051 --> 22:35.816
Hm?

22:38.423 --> 22:39.721
Hm.

22:39.791 --> 22:41.953
Stupid toothpaste lid.

22:52.971 --> 22:55.600
Hrumph! Give me that!

23:18.730 --> 23:20.631
All right,
so life's not perfect.

23:20.699 --> 23:23.032
I did get to meet
the girl of my dreams.

23:23.101 --> 23:26.435
Tomorrow, it will be better.

23:29.641 --> 23:32.736
Wish tomorrow could be better
for me, too, big guy.

23:32.811 --> 23:35.076
Sammy, what's the matter?

23:35.147 --> 23:38.174
I'm not feeling it.
This isn't fun.

23:38.450 --> 23:39.850
You're avenging your brother.

23:39.918 --> 23:42.752
The fun part is just... fun.

23:43.688 --> 23:44.815
Sam!

23:44.890 --> 23:49.055
Let him go! He has to figure
this out by himself.

23:50.862 --> 23:54.424
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

24:08.780 --> 24:10.510
How's he doing?

24:10.582 --> 24:12.551
He's doing much better, Samuel.

24:23.261 --> 24:26.060
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

24:32.704 --> 24:33.899
(CHUCKLING)

24:33.972 --> 24:37.204
Sam? Sam!

24:37.275 --> 24:39.506
I haven't seen you in forever.

24:39.578 --> 24:40.739
How are you?

24:40.812 --> 24:41.905
I'm great.

24:41.980 --> 24:44.643
You look... stunning.

24:44.716 --> 24:47.049
Why thank you, fair prince.

24:48.887 --> 24:51.721
I've missed... well,
I've missed being here.

24:53.625 --> 24:55.218
I've missed you, too.

24:55.293 --> 24:58.923
Sam, you've just missed
the craziest thing.

24:58.997 --> 25:00.727
It was insane!

25:00.799 --> 25:02.927
Pixie Tom, you know,
the slug farmer?

25:03.001 --> 25:05.232
Was flipping his lid!

25:05.303 --> 25:10.071
I opened up the gate,
and it's like, Slug-apalooza!

25:10.141 --> 25:11.700
You've gotta see this.

25:11.776 --> 25:14.746
No, Twitch...
I don't gotta see that.

25:14.813 --> 25:17.146
I want to mingle
with my Pixies for once.

25:17.215 --> 25:20.743
Oh... oh...

25:20.819 --> 25:22.947
Um... hey, Daisy!

25:23.021 --> 25:24.649
Hi, Twitch.

25:24.723 --> 25:27.249
Nice to see you and Max
haven't changed.

25:27.325 --> 25:29.260
I think that was an insult.

25:29.327 --> 25:31.887
Ah, it's gotta be a compliment.

25:31.963 --> 25:33.727
That was a compliment, right?

25:33.798 --> 25:35.994
Not in your wildest dreams.

25:36.067 --> 25:39.868
Hey, Sam, we never
got that date.

25:39.938 --> 25:42.134
How about we zip
to the glow worm trail?

25:42.207 --> 25:43.835
Without your buddies.

25:43.909 --> 25:46.071
Sure, that's great.

25:47.245 --> 25:49.680
Wait! What about the curse?

25:49.748 --> 25:52.718
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

26:14.639 --> 26:15.902
Hello?

26:15.974 --> 26:19.741
Hello? Sir?

26:19.811 --> 26:21.143
Are you here?

26:21.212 --> 26:24.205
Distraction!

26:24.282 --> 26:28.083
Well? Whoa? Whoo!

26:28.153 --> 26:30.816
It's Samuel,
he's in the village.

26:30.889 --> 26:33.654
He's... Not with the human?

26:33.725 --> 26:35.125
Take me to him, at once!

26:35.193 --> 26:37.856
That boy has a lesson to learn.

26:37.929 --> 26:40.023
You've really surprised me.

26:40.098 --> 26:41.862
I thought I'd never
see you again.

26:41.933 --> 26:44.266
You can't keep the prodigal son
away from home forever.

26:44.336 --> 26:46.237
So what's it like?

26:46.304 --> 26:48.239
Being on the outside
all the time?

26:48.306 --> 26:49.706
A lot less fun.

26:49.774 --> 26:53.040
Humans live to work and there's
no one to really talk to.

26:53.111 --> 26:54.111
No?

26:54.179 --> 26:56.307
What about Bumble Dee
and Bumble Dumb?

26:56.381 --> 27:00.682
Well, they're dependable, but I think you
summed them up pretty well yourself.

27:00.752 --> 27:04.348
Well, I don't see them
around. Do you?

27:04.422 --> 27:06.914
I suppose not.

27:14.899 --> 27:16.333
Ow! That's two.

27:16.401 --> 27:18.097
Want to go for a third?

27:18.169 --> 27:20.729
No... you slap too hard.

27:20.805 --> 27:22.398
That's the point.

27:22.674 --> 27:26.338
Yeah, well, how about
if I gave you a dead wing?

27:28.446 --> 27:30.813
Oh! My funny bone!

27:30.882 --> 27:34.944
I'm genuinely surprised, all that extra
you doesn't work like an air bag.

27:40.058 --> 27:42.118
I think Sammy's in trouble.

27:43.061 --> 27:45.292
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

27:45.363 --> 27:47.332
( RUSTLING) Wow...

27:47.399 --> 27:49.698
spoiling the moment... again.

27:49.768 --> 27:52.067
Sam, your dad, he's...

27:52.137 --> 27:53.161
Super mad...

27:53.238 --> 27:55.798
likeveins-bursting-
from-his-head mad.

27:55.874 --> 27:56.967
And he's...

27:57.042 --> 28:01.002
Standing in the presence
of the disgrace I call my son.

28:01.079 --> 28:03.378
Dad, I... Save it!

28:03.448 --> 28:07.180
When I make a declaration,
I stand by my decree.

28:07.252 --> 28:10.154
Here you are making
a fool of yourself...

28:10.221 --> 28:11.951
and making a fool
of this family!

28:12.023 --> 28:13.457
It's not like that, Dad.

28:13.725 --> 28:16.889
Oh, no? Then please explain
to me what this is...

28:16.961 --> 28:20.864
because what I see is a son
disobeying his father...

28:20.932 --> 28:24.801
so he can trounce around
with some questionable girl.

28:24.869 --> 28:26.098
Some, girl?

28:26.171 --> 28:28.197
Don't you dare raise your voice
to me, young man!

28:28.273 --> 28:30.071
All you care about is vengeance!

28:30.141 --> 28:31.336
What about love, Dad?

28:31.409 --> 28:34.846
Did you ever think that maybe it would
be nice if I fell in love? Did you?

28:34.913 --> 28:36.905
Love? (CHUCKLES)

28:36.981 --> 28:40.042
You don't know a thing
about love.

28:40.118 --> 28:44.317
Love is when you build a kingdom
with your bare hands...

28:44.389 --> 28:46.085
to impress a woman.

28:47.192 --> 28:53.325
You spend 110 years of your life
raising two heirs to the throne...

28:53.398 --> 28:57.165
and when someone takes that all
away from you, you make them pay!

28:57.235 --> 29:01.172
And too scared to exact that
revenge yourself, you send me.

29:01.239 --> 29:03.208
Get out of my kingdom.

29:03.274 --> 29:04.401
Dad...

29:04.476 --> 29:08.379
Get out, leave!
And don't come back.

29:08.947 --> 29:10.848
Dad?

29:12.117 --> 29:13.346
Sammy?

29:13.418 --> 29:15.148
I have to go.

29:20.992 --> 29:23.052
Awkward.

29:23.128 --> 29:26.088
<i>(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

29:26.164 --> 29:28.531
Stupid curse, you want me
to ruin a guy's life?

29:28.800 --> 29:31.964
Is that what you want? Fine.

29:52.557 --> 29:56.085
(ALARM CLOCK BLARING)

30:02.391 --> 30:03.911
(SQUIRREL CHITTERING)
[JOE] What the...

30:03.935 --> 30:05.961
[JOE] How'd a squirrel get
in here? Those aren't nuts!

30:06.037 --> 30:07.835
( LOUD CRUNCHING)
[JOE] Wait, ow!

30:07.906 --> 30:11.343
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

30:11.409 --> 30:14.846
( HUMMING)

30:16.281 --> 30:18.011
Ah, toast.

30:22.453 --> 30:24.115
Good morning, Mr. Bluebird.

30:24.189 --> 30:27.318
Your friend here had a little
success with the ladies.

30:29.027 --> 30:32.054
Surprised? I know, so was I.

30:32.130 --> 30:34.998
I think today is gonna
be a brand-new start for Joe.

30:35.533 --> 30:37.058
Huh?

30:37.135 --> 30:39.502
Agh! Hot!

30:39.571 --> 30:41.199
It's hot!

30:46.110 --> 30:48.409
Agh! Fire! Fire!

30:53.484 --> 30:55.180
(GROANS)

30:58.089 --> 30:59.887
Stupid nature.

30:59.958 --> 31:01.517
What a mess?

31:01.593 --> 31:03.562
Why me?

31:03.628 --> 31:06.223
(CLINKING)

31:06.297 --> 31:08.027
Huh... hello?

31:11.669 --> 31:13.262
Footprints?

31:13.338 --> 31:14.966
(GASPING) Ah... ah...

31:21.346 --> 31:22.541
Hey!

31:22.614 --> 31:25.277
Wh... did you just talk?

31:27.652 --> 31:29.052
You just talked.

31:29.120 --> 31:32.147
You said, "Hey." I heard you!

31:32.223 --> 31:34.454
What are you?

31:34.525 --> 31:38.087
I'm not letting you out of there
until you tell me what you are.

31:38.162 --> 31:41.155
Fine, I'm here to give you a memo
from the flies in your kitchen.

31:41.232 --> 31:42.996
They're forming a union.

31:43.067 --> 31:46.333
You can talk! How? What are you?

31:46.404 --> 31:49.602
I'm a figment
of your imagination.

31:49.674 --> 31:51.472
Now go see your psychiatrist.

31:51.542 --> 31:54.535
Atalking bumble bee?
What a smart aleck.

31:54.612 --> 31:57.548
Do I look like a bumble bee?
They're fuzzy.

31:57.615 --> 32:01.052
Wish I had a stinger, though.
I'd sting you with my butt.

32:01.119 --> 32:03.987
A few more hours in there and
you'll take me more seriously.

32:12.997 --> 32:14.693
(CLEARS THROAT) Okay, okay...

32:14.966 --> 32:18.130
I'm a pixie, okay,
see the wings?

32:18.202 --> 32:20.364
Huh... why are you
in my kitchen?

32:20.438 --> 32:24.637
I'm... um, I'm fulfilling
an obligation to my people.

32:24.709 --> 32:26.473
Obligation?

32:26.544 --> 32:29.514
You have been cursed.

32:29.580 --> 32:31.344
Yeah, tell me about it.

32:31.416 --> 32:34.113
We cursed you.

32:34.185 --> 32:35.676
Hm?

32:35.753 --> 32:40.350
You dumped some garbage into the ravine
and my brother is still badly hurt.

32:40.425 --> 32:43.623
You nearly killed me and
destroyed half our village.

32:43.695 --> 32:45.596
You've been cursed ever since.

32:45.663 --> 32:48.258
All this time, it's been you?

32:48.333 --> 32:50.359
Every time I fell
or ran into stuff?

32:50.435 --> 32:52.165
All the trips to the hospital?

32:52.236 --> 32:56.367
All the embarrassing, humiliating
moments when... it was you?

32:56.441 --> 32:58.603
Why? Why would you
do that to me?

32:58.676 --> 33:00.440
I told you, when you...

33:00.511 --> 33:03.447
Because I dumped garbage
into a river?

33:03.514 --> 33:07.076
I know, I... look, it's just
the way we do things.

33:08.319 --> 33:10.083
Wait, no!
You can't leave me here!

33:10.154 --> 33:13.454
I'm not letting you screw
up my life anymore!

33:15.526 --> 33:18.724
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

33:31.376 --> 33:34.005
Ahh.

33:34.078 --> 33:35.273
Hm.

33:44.188 --> 33:46.680
Okay, this is gonna be okay.

33:46.758 --> 33:51.423
Any minute now, Max and Twitch
will arrive to save me.

33:51.496 --> 33:55.558
Whoo-hoo! Whoo-hoo!

33:55.633 --> 33:57.363
(SIGHING)

33:57.435 --> 34:00.269
Yup, any minute now.

34:02.840 --> 34:04.433
Hey, Dad, lookin' sharp.

34:04.509 --> 34:07.570
Joe, we agreed you weren't
supposed to be in here.

34:07.645 --> 34:10.478
Now get back to the desk
and answer the phones!

34:10.547 --> 34:12.574
Check the ignition cables?

34:12.650 --> 34:16.815
Yeah, I checked all the cables,
replaced the fuel pump, the starter.

34:17.031 --> 34:18.831
Give her another start.
( ENGINE TURNING OVER)

34:18.856 --> 34:20.415
Try it again.

34:20.491 --> 34:22.391
Joe, I'm warning you.

34:22.460 --> 34:24.395
And... that should do it?

34:24.462 --> 34:26.293
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

34:26.364 --> 34:27.797
What's next, Pops?

34:29.634 --> 34:31.603
Hee-yaw!

34:33.103 --> 34:35.232
He shoots... he scores!

34:36.507 --> 34:40.342
Hee-yaw! Hee-yaw!

34:42.346 --> 34:44.212
Huh.

34:45.483 --> 34:47.384
Whoa! Whoa...

34:48.453 --> 34:50.114
I got it! I got it!

34:54.891 --> 34:56.121
Diddah!

34:56.194 --> 34:58.686
Hee-yaw...

34:58.763 --> 35:00.322
Help.

35:01.599 --> 35:03.795
Hey, Joe! Yeah?

35:03.868 --> 35:06.201
That was pretty incredible
back there.

35:06.270 --> 35:07.329
Yeah?

35:07.405 --> 35:09.806
Yeah, remember that promotion
we were talking about?

35:09.874 --> 35:12.139
Yeah. Well, let's do it.

35:12.210 --> 35:13.610
How about floor manager?

35:13.678 --> 35:16.671
Really? You even have
tomorrow off to celebrate.

35:16.747 --> 35:18.648
Why don't you go
meet a nice girl?

35:18.716 --> 35:20.077
Already one step ahead
of you, Dad.

35:20.151 --> 35:22.347
Oh, so that's
what's got you goin'.

35:22.420 --> 35:24.616
I'm working on it.

35:24.689 --> 35:27.454
Whoo-hoo! Whoo-hoo!

35:27.525 --> 35:29.790
Whoo! Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

35:29.861 --> 35:31.420
Go, Little Goobers!

35:31.496 --> 35:34.466
I swear by all that is holy...

35:34.532 --> 35:36.626
if you don't get off my slug...

35:36.701 --> 35:38.602
Agh!

35:38.669 --> 35:42.299
This pitch fork is goin
g where the sun don't shine!

35:43.474 --> 35:47.570
That was awesome!
Sammy would have loved that.

35:47.645 --> 35:50.274
Hey, where is Sammy?

35:50.348 --> 35:54.376
Sam? Yeah, uh, Sam.

35:54.452 --> 35:55.784
Where are you?

35:59.790 --> 36:02.191
I see him. Where?

36:02.260 --> 36:04.695
Over there,
he's underneath that glass.

36:04.762 --> 36:07.630
What the heck
is he doing in there?

36:07.698 --> 36:09.189
Ssh!

36:09.267 --> 36:10.826
I'm trying to figure it out.

36:13.204 --> 36:15.605
Really? Do you have
to do that now?

36:15.673 --> 36:18.802
What? Slug riding
always makes me hungry.

36:18.876 --> 36:20.538
Is there anything that doesn't?

36:20.611 --> 36:25.447
Diets... no, wait,
those make me super hungry.

36:25.516 --> 36:28.418
Wake up! Sam!

36:28.486 --> 36:30.955
He's not moving.

36:35.826 --> 36:38.694
Whoa! Look who's all smiles
and happy time.

36:38.763 --> 36:41.665
And he's here to share a little
of that happy time...

36:41.732 --> 36:43.894
with the lady he's been
thinking about all day.

36:43.968 --> 36:46.267
Referring to yourself
in the third person?

36:46.337 --> 36:48.306
This has to be something major.

36:48.372 --> 36:49.670
I'll give you one guess.

36:49.740 --> 36:52.539
Who's got two thumbs, one eye
and a promotion at work?

36:52.610 --> 36:53.703
Ooh, who?

36:53.778 --> 36:56.714
This guy right here.

36:56.781 --> 37:00.411
Stop, Joe! Put me down,
I'm gonna hurl!

37:00.484 --> 37:03.352
I just got promoted to the
manager of the car garage.

37:03.421 --> 37:07.381
Nothing I'd rather do than take you
out for a nice, celebration dinner.

37:07.458 --> 37:08.687
What do you say?

37:08.759 --> 37:11.285
Ah, absolutely. Yes!

37:11.362 --> 37:13.490
III pick you up at 7:00 sharp.

37:24.809 --> 37:28.473
Do you think he's <i>... muerto?</i>

37:28.546 --> 37:29.707
Don't say that.

37:30.848 --> 37:34.444
Sam? Sammy? You alive in there?

37:34.518 --> 37:36.350
Twitch... Max...

37:36.420 --> 37:39.549
Oh, man, I had the worst dream.

37:39.624 --> 37:41.456
No dream, I was caught!

37:41.525 --> 37:43.086
Twitch, Max, thank goodness
you're here!

37:52.436 --> 37:54.496
You guys gotta hide. Great.

37:57.775 --> 38:00.506
Hey! Guess what?
I had the perfect day.

38:00.578 --> 38:04.572
Not a single incident, all thanks
to this little, glass jail.

38:04.649 --> 38:07.016
Little guy knocked himself out
trying to escape.

38:07.084 --> 38:08.518
Tenacious.

38:20.064 --> 38:21.623
That was mine!

38:23.334 --> 38:24.529
Coast is clear.

38:24.602 --> 38:26.332
Hoo-hoo-cah-choo!

38:26.404 --> 38:27.838
He can see us, dummy!

38:27.905 --> 38:29.840
Look, I almost got out
of here all on my own.

38:29.907 --> 38:31.671
With the three of us
working together...

38:31.742 --> 38:34.075
we should have no problem
knocking this thing over.

38:34.345 --> 38:37.440
Okay, got it. Yo comprende.

38:37.515 --> 38:42.920
Um, on the boring days, I've been reading
Joe's Spanish-English dictionary.

38:45.723 --> 38:47.521
On the count of three, we push.

38:47.591 --> 38:50.993
One, two, three!

38:51.996 --> 38:53.464
Harder!

38:57.802 --> 39:01.466
Everything hurts!

39:01.539 --> 39:02.563
But we're almost there.

39:02.640 --> 39:04.438
One more push.

39:04.508 --> 39:07.068
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

39:07.144 --> 39:13.050
Ah-comite-comite-cora!
Ah-comite-comite-cora!

39:13.117 --> 39:14.710
Tay-nay-tay, tah-nah-tah...

39:14.785 --> 39:17.983
Hooru-hooru, nah-nah-ti-ti-ti...

39:18.055 --> 39:19.489
Wakka-fi-fi-fay.

39:19.557 --> 39:21.583
Harooha-harooha...

39:21.659 --> 39:24.993
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

39:32.103 --> 39:33.503
He's waking up!

39:33.571 --> 39:36.666
Oh... what time is it?

39:36.741 --> 39:37.741
Hey, there's more!

39:37.742 --> 39:40.837
Run, you fools!
Sam, use your wings!

39:40.911 --> 39:44.006
Right... but it was just... it was
so much more dramatic this way.

39:44.081 --> 39:45.879
Let's get out of here!

39:47.051 --> 39:49.384
Stop!

39:49.453 --> 39:50.614
I missed my date.

39:50.688 --> 39:52.816
I missed my date with Michelle!

39:54.959 --> 39:57.087
This is all your fault.

40:00.097 --> 40:02.089
[JOE] Get back here!

40:02.666 --> 40:04.601
(GROWLING)

40:19.483 --> 40:21.816
That was really close.

40:21.886 --> 40:25.982
Look, guys, I'm... I'm sorry
about what I said before.

40:26.056 --> 40:27.854
You were there for me.

40:27.925 --> 40:29.894
You're my best friends.

40:29.960 --> 40:32.520
I'm sorry... bring it in.

40:33.531 --> 40:35.124
Oop, that's a little tight, Max.

40:35.699 --> 40:37.463
(GROWLING)

40:37.535 --> 40:38.969
(GASPING)

40:39.036 --> 40:41.870
You! Fly. Everybody fly!

40:44.875 --> 40:46.776
Yo, 'Zilla!

40:46.844 --> 40:50.645
(ALARM SOUNDING)
( PIXIES SCREAMING)

40:56.787 --> 40:58.722
Wow.

41:04.595 --> 41:05.688
You!

41:05.763 --> 41:06.822
(GASPING)

41:10.000 --> 41:12.731
I just want to be left alone!

41:12.803 --> 41:15.238
I missed the perfect date
with the girl of my dreams...

41:15.506 --> 41:17.134
because of you and your trap!

41:17.208 --> 41:18.208
That was mine.

41:18.275 --> 41:22.212
Yeah? That was your trick,
here's mine.

41:26.217 --> 41:28.914
( PIXIES SCREAMING)

41:34.091 --> 41:35.252
Stay away!

41:41.866 --> 41:44.859
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

41:44.935 --> 41:46.215
I didn't mean
for this to happen.

41:46.237 --> 41:48.069
Oh, but it did.

41:48.138 --> 41:51.165
Not only does this outsider
know we exist...

41:51.242 --> 41:55.577
but he has destroyed everything
I've worked so hard to build.

41:55.646 --> 41:57.945
Dad, I'm so sorry.

41:58.015 --> 41:59.847
This is all my fault.

42:05.089 --> 42:06.921
<i>(MUSIC CHANGES)</i>

42:06.991 --> 42:08.653
Agh!

42:12.963 --> 42:15.023
<i>[MICHELLE]</i>
<i>Hey, Joe, it's Michelle.</i>

42:15.099 --> 42:19.662
<i>I'm really looking forward to tonight and
I will see you in about 20 minutes. Bye.</i>

42:19.737 --> 42:22.536
<i>Hey, Joe, it's a little past</i>
<i>7:00 now...</i>

42:22.606 --> 42:24.905
<i>and I was just wondering</i>
<i>if you were running late.</i>

42:24.975 --> 42:26.204
<i>Call me back.</i>

42:26.277 --> 42:29.543
<i>Joe, it's 7:20, and I hope</i>
<i>everything's okay...</i>

42:29.613 --> 42:32.242
<i>considering how we met.</i>

42:32.316 --> 42:34.876
<i>Look, buddy, it's 7:30</i>
<i>and you are still not here.</i>

42:34.952 --> 42:37.319
<i>Seriously? Call me.</i>

42:37.588 --> 42:41.320
<i>Listen, I'm not trying to sound</i>
<i>psycho here, but it's 7:45.</i>

42:41.592 --> 42:43.083
<i>Where are you?</i>

42:43.160 --> 42:46.028
<i>Joe Beck, you stood me up,</i>
<i>you're a jerk!</i>

42:49.333 --> 42:51.825
( PHONE RINGING)

42:52.870 --> 42:55.032
What? Hey...

42:55.105 --> 42:56.129
Michelle?

42:56.206 --> 42:57.834
Yeah, what do you want?

42:57.908 --> 42:59.968
I just wanted to apologize for...

43:00.044 --> 43:01.774
Oh, for being a jerk face?

43:01.845 --> 43:04.280
No! Yes... wait, listen...

43:04.348 --> 43:07.079
I just ran into
a little car trouble.

43:07.151 --> 43:08.949
Aren't you a mechanic?

43:09.019 --> 43:11.147
<i>Yeah, but... look...</i>

43:11.221 --> 43:16.785
I think you're great, and I'm hoping you're
sweet enough to give me another chance.

43:16.860 --> 43:19.261
Okay, meet me at the
Horn of Plenty tomorrow at noon.

43:19.330 --> 43:21.128
That's the vegan restaurant,
right?

43:21.198 --> 43:23.360
This time I won't let you down,
I promise!

43:23.634 --> 43:25.967
Yeah, you'd regret it.

43:29.306 --> 43:32.242
This means war, you know?

43:32.309 --> 43:36.110
Hey, Dad, maybe we just do what
he says and leave him alone?

43:36.180 --> 43:37.307
Excuse me?

43:37.381 --> 43:39.145
Uh, who do you think you are?

43:39.216 --> 43:41.947
I am your son,
and so is William...

43:42.019 --> 43:44.955
and he would never approve of
what we've done to this human.

43:45.022 --> 43:49.050
Well, Samuel, tell me, what
would William have approved?

43:49.126 --> 43:53.188
Would he have approved of you bringing
death and destruction upon our kind?

43:53.263 --> 43:55.994
He would have talked to the
human, reasoned with him.

43:56.066 --> 44:02.996
Reason? You ask for a reason, your brother may
not see another sunrise and you need a reason.

44:03.073 --> 44:06.237
We Pixies do not reason
with our enemies...

44:06.310 --> 44:07.938
we are survivors,
we are fighters...

44:08.012 --> 44:12.177
and we will exact revenge
and uphold our traditions.

44:12.249 --> 44:15.048
We ruined that human's life.

44:15.119 --> 44:18.146
It's our tradition that caused
this destruction.

44:18.222 --> 44:23.251
No, no, it was a boy who refused
the commands of his king...

44:23.327 --> 44:25.922
a son who ignored his father.

44:25.996 --> 44:28.932
I am here to keep
all of us safe.

44:28.999 --> 44:31.867
That is why I wear the crown.

44:31.935 --> 44:33.801
You need to exact revenge!

44:33.871 --> 44:38.775
We the Pixies
declare war on Joe!

44:38.842 --> 44:41.243
I guess you're right,
I'll do it.

44:42.980 --> 44:45.916
You made the right choice,
my son.

44:45.983 --> 44:48.976
Pixies! Brothers! Sisters!

44:49.053 --> 44:51.352
Prepare yourselves for war!

44:51.422 --> 44:54.449
( LOUD COMMOTION )

44:58.762 --> 45:01.960
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

45:03.133 --> 45:07.161
<i>(LOUNGE MUSIC PLAYING)</i>
Mm-hm. Hmm.

45:17.948 --> 45:20.213
(CLEARS THROAT)

45:23.787 --> 45:27.121
( HUMMING)

45:27.191 --> 45:30.389
(ALL YELLING)

45:41.371 --> 45:44.364
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

45:46.810 --> 45:47.971
(CAR HORN HONKING)

45:48.045 --> 45:49.377
Hey, thank you.

45:49.446 --> 45:52.211
Sorry to keep you waiting,
I had car trouble.

45:52.282 --> 45:54.274
I thought you didn't drive?
Gotcha.

45:54.351 --> 45:55.944
Come on, let's go inside.

45:56.019 --> 45:57.248
What's on your tie?

45:57.321 --> 45:58.983
It's a Kathulu.

45:59.056 --> 46:00.115
Gesundheit.

46:00.190 --> 46:01.886
No, no, it's a Kathulu.

46:01.959 --> 46:05.396
It's a cosmic entity that's a mix
of human, dragon and octopus.

46:05.462 --> 46:07.454
Oh, that Kathulu.

46:07.531 --> 46:09.261
Yeah, he's awesome, right?

46:09.333 --> 46:10.392
Yeah.

46:13.871 --> 46:17.035
Welcome to the Horn of Plenty...

46:17.107 --> 46:22.102
where food is thy medicine
and medicine is thy food.

46:22.179 --> 46:25.343
My name is Alex and I
will be your server.

46:25.415 --> 46:28.385
Please look over our menu.

46:28.452 --> 46:30.444
Well, there's a chipper,
young lad.

46:30.521 --> 46:34.788
Oh, yeah, he looks thrilled
to be here.

46:34.858 --> 46:36.850
Agh! Are you kidding me!

46:36.927 --> 46:39.863
What? Oh, uh, the menu!

46:39.930 --> 46:42.957
They have, uh, durian.

46:43.033 --> 46:44.262
Oh, you like durian?

46:44.334 --> 46:45.996
Sure, yeah, love it.

46:46.069 --> 46:48.436
Uh, just like Mom used to make.

46:53.510 --> 46:56.105
I've, uh... it's a ritual I have.

46:56.180 --> 46:59.844
I use the menu
and I slam it shut.

46:59.917 --> 47:02.546
Then I... I work it like
a butterfly...

47:02.619 --> 47:06.351
and I get the aroma
of the kitchen in.

47:06.423 --> 47:10.292
Mm.
Um, I've never heard of that.

47:10.360 --> 47:11.885
Mm.

47:11.962 --> 47:15.956
Oh, wow, you are so right.
I can totally smell the miso.

47:18.101 --> 47:19.262
Look out!

47:23.140 --> 47:26.042
A fig? Are you hungry, sir?

47:26.109 --> 47:28.476
How about I bring you
some bread?

47:31.982 --> 47:33.974
Are you... okay?

47:34.051 --> 47:37.920
Yeah, I had a horrible
experience at Christmas once.

47:37.988 --> 47:40.924
Figs were involved...
it didn't end well.

47:40.991 --> 47:44.223
Ugh, tell me about it, the
holidays can be pretty traumatic.

47:44.294 --> 47:48.595
This one time, my mom and I were decorating
our tree when my dad came in and, um...

47:53.070 --> 47:54.070
Agh!

47:54.137 --> 47:57.266
Your bread... and what
will you be having today?

47:57.341 --> 47:59.936
Ooh, I'll have the organic
Portobello sandwich...

48:00.010 --> 48:03.947
with a side of vegan soy
and tofu fries, please. Joe?

48:04.014 --> 48:06.643
Uh, I'll have the same.
Does it come with bacon?

48:06.917 --> 48:08.909
Meat is death.

48:08.986 --> 48:10.249
Hold the bacon.

48:10.320 --> 48:13.085
Everything all right, Joe?

48:13.156 --> 48:14.556
Yup, yup, doing good.

48:14.625 --> 48:17.185
Just keeping an eye out
for more figs.

48:18.161 --> 48:22.030
Well, anyway, so we were
decorating our tree, when...

48:24.601 --> 48:27.230
Oh, it's on! Let's do this!

48:27.304 --> 48:28.431
What are you talking about?

48:28.505 --> 48:33.341
Oh, it's on...
the animal shelter.

48:33.410 --> 48:35.174
It's on, it's open.

48:35.245 --> 48:37.510
Let's go to the animal shelter.

48:37.581 --> 48:40.676
Oh, that is so incredible, yes,
let's go there right now.

48:40.951 --> 48:44.479
Look, I'll cancel our order and we can
go to my parents' for dinner later.

48:44.554 --> 48:48.992
This is getting out of control.
I said stay away!

48:52.596 --> 48:54.690
Don't you just love the smell
of the animal shelter?

48:54.965 --> 48:58.299
Oh, yeah. Love that smell
of... wet dog?

48:58.368 --> 49:00.564
( RETCHING)

49:01.638 --> 49:05.302
If I had it my way, humans would be
locked up and the animals would be free.

49:05.375 --> 49:06.934
So you're a trouble maker.

49:07.010 --> 49:09.536
What? No! I'm not
a trouble maker.

49:15.285 --> 49:17.311
( DOG BARKS, GROWLS)

49:20.357 --> 49:22.189
(CHOKING)

49:22.259 --> 49:24.091
Ooh! Hold that pose!

49:28.065 --> 49:29.328
Done!

49:32.302 --> 49:35.033
You had that pair of scissors
there the entire time?

49:35.105 --> 49:37.336
A good artist
is always prepared.

49:37.407 --> 49:39.376
It made for a great sketch.
What the...

49:39.443 --> 49:41.412
How do you... it's amazing!

49:41.478 --> 49:43.118
What's amazing is that
you didn't get bit.

49:43.146 --> 49:44.444
(GROWLING)

49:44.514 --> 49:49.316
Speaking of biting, my parents are having
dinner at 5:00, if you're still hungry.

49:49.386 --> 49:51.378
Uh, meeting the parents already.

49:51.455 --> 49:53.720
I actually think my mom will
really like you. (GASPS)

49:53.790 --> 49:56.350
My dad, on the other hand, he's
a bit harder to get to know.

49:56.426 --> 49:57.985
Hold that thought.

49:59.629 --> 50:01.757
Don't you dare! Joe, what?

50:02.032 --> 50:04.058
What is it? (GROWLING)

50:07.671 --> 50:11.699
No, no, no, no! No! Agh!

50:11.775 --> 50:13.744
Aw, Joe, that is so sweet.

50:13.810 --> 50:16.245
I mean, you can't stand to see
that little puppy in here.

50:16.313 --> 50:18.282
You're saving him
from these oppressors!

50:18.348 --> 50:20.249
[MICHELLE] That was your plan
the entire time.

50:20.317 --> 50:24.584
Uh... absolutely! Eh...

50:29.426 --> 50:32.362
Hey, Joe, are you sure
you're cool with this?

50:32.429 --> 50:34.728
I know it's a bit early to be
meeting my parents and all and...

50:34.798 --> 50:37.529
Yeah, I'm looking forward
to it. Why?

50:37.601 --> 50:40.537
Well, you just seem
a bit... distant.

50:40.604 --> 50:46.339
Uh, I'm just picturing how wonderful your
parents must be if they raised a girl like you.

50:47.477 --> 50:49.412
Let's just head inside, shall
we?

50:51.314 --> 50:53.545
Namaste.

50:53.617 --> 50:55.609
Thank you, I think I shall stay.

50:55.685 --> 50:58.814
My word, he's so precious.

50:59.089 --> 51:01.820
Gail, don't scare the boy before
I've had a chance to meet him.

51:02.092 --> 51:06.393
Help me with the tofu,
it's getting unwieldy!

51:06.463 --> 51:09.262
You did fantastic
with this one, Michelle.

51:09.332 --> 51:12.359
Not like that last boy you brought
over, with the piercings...

51:12.436 --> 51:15.133
and that loud carbon-emitting
death trap he was driving.

51:15.205 --> 51:17.504
Gail! Coming!

51:17.574 --> 51:19.372
I had to come from somewhere.

51:19.443 --> 51:21.412
You didn't want
to warn me first?

51:21.478 --> 51:23.777
( DOG GROWLS)

51:24.514 --> 51:28.383
All hail King Pixie!

51:28.452 --> 51:31.320
( PIXIES CHEERING)

51:31.388 --> 51:36.292
For too long, we have been pushed
to the edges of this world.

51:36.359 --> 51:40.592
We live in the ruins
of the temple that was nature.

51:40.664 --> 51:43.156
The humans continue
to force us back...

51:43.233 --> 51:47.136
with their growing gluttony
of technology and garbage.

51:48.505 --> 51:50.838
But no more, my pixie warriors!

51:50.907 --> 51:54.503
No more! Today, we make a stand!

51:54.578 --> 51:59.846
Today we strike back at the very
core of indecency and woe...

51:59.916 --> 52:04.286
that has beset our tribes
for generations.

52:04.354 --> 52:09.691
Today we will strike down the
auto mechanic known as Joe.

52:12.295 --> 52:16.528
For the glory of Pixies!

52:16.600 --> 52:18.330
He's incredible!

52:18.401 --> 52:20.495
I wish my mom was here
to see this.

52:20.570 --> 52:22.334
Max, she's right over there.

52:22.405 --> 52:24.169
Hey, Max!

52:24.241 --> 52:25.903
Oh... hi, Mom!

52:26.176 --> 52:29.613
Are you ready for war, Sam?
Uh... Sam?

52:29.679 --> 52:31.705
I have a bad feeling about this.

52:34.184 --> 52:38.280
And this is the kitchen,
the stone is from Argentina...

52:38.355 --> 52:42.156
and most of the decor
hails from Africa.

52:42.225 --> 52:44.194
Having trouble keeping up
with Mom?

52:44.261 --> 52:45.627
Who me? I'm good.

52:45.695 --> 52:48.563
Pretty sure the speed walking
wore holes in my shoes, though.

52:48.632 --> 52:50.533
Oh, oh, a Canadian.

52:50.600 --> 52:54.332
Hey, Joe, what do you call
a cow with no legs?

52:54.404 --> 52:55.565
Oh, Dad, please don't.

52:55.639 --> 52:56.937
What?

52:57.207 --> 53:00.871
Ground beef!
Because the cow is on the...

53:00.944 --> 53:03.311
(CLEARS THROAT)
I think the boy gets it, dear.

53:03.380 --> 53:09.286
Okay, okay, it also wouldn't hurt to
have real beef every once in a while.

53:09.352 --> 53:11.548
That's enough, Captain Cannibal.

53:11.621 --> 53:13.783
Do I look like someone
who'd eat people?

53:13.857 --> 53:15.758
I'd never eat a person...

53:15.825 --> 53:19.387
unless you consider
the talking cow a person.

53:19.462 --> 53:22.921
In which case, I might just be
persuaded to give it a try.

53:22.999 --> 53:24.297
I think they like you.

53:24.367 --> 53:26.700
As long as your dad doesn't
toss me on the grill.

53:26.770 --> 53:27.897
(GIGGLES)

53:27.971 --> 53:30.304
Just grab a tray.

53:32.542 --> 53:35.637
Cheap thing won't light.

53:35.712 --> 53:37.374
So what's your deal, Joe?

53:37.447 --> 53:41.282
Oh, I'm an auto mechanic.
I actually just got a promotion.

53:41.351 --> 53:42.910
That's great!

53:42.986 --> 53:46.980
You hear that, Gail? This hard-working
boy just got a promotion.

53:47.257 --> 53:49.817
This is moving fast, isn't it?

53:49.893 --> 53:52.920
Oh, so what? I met your father
on a Tuesday...

53:52.996 --> 53:55.397
and a week later,
we were married in Vegas.

53:55.465 --> 53:57.229
Well, I'm definitely
not ready for marriage.

53:57.300 --> 54:01.294
He's cute, funny, seems like
he's got things together...

54:01.371 --> 54:04.239
and it would be nice
to have grandkids around.

54:04.307 --> 54:05.775
Okay, slow down, Mom!

54:05.842 --> 54:09.677
I just can't get this
lighter going!

54:09.746 --> 54:13.615
Here, let me try. Hm...

54:13.683 --> 54:15.743
Hmm.

54:19.656 --> 54:21.921
That's some bad luck, son.

54:21.992 --> 54:23.551
Bad luck?

54:27.063 --> 54:28.861
Oh, no!

54:28.932 --> 54:32.528
Okay, girls! Joe's got
the hot stones going.

54:32.602 --> 54:34.730
What happened to your eyebrows?

54:34.804 --> 54:36.966
Uh, pyrotechnic mishap.

54:37.040 --> 54:41.375
How in the world did a grease monkey
like you become such a charmer?

54:41.444 --> 54:43.436
Just lucky, I guess.

54:43.513 --> 54:47.314
Huh. Joe, not sure if you've
ever done hot stones before...

54:47.384 --> 54:48.647
but dinner takes a while.

54:48.718 --> 54:50.880
What we do to keep things
moving is play a game.

54:50.954 --> 54:53.014
How about boys versus girls?

54:53.089 --> 54:54.648
Mom!

54:54.724 --> 55:01.289
Your call, Joe, or are you afraid
of getting crushed by the girls?

55:03.466 --> 55:06.334
Uh, sure, yeah, I'm in.

55:06.403 --> 55:08.372
For William!

55:08.438 --> 55:11.670
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

55:11.741 --> 55:13.039
Get over...

55:17.113 --> 55:18.843
Is the game Charades?

55:18.915 --> 55:22.784
I don't think so.

55:22.852 --> 55:25.048
Then what is he doing?

55:25.121 --> 55:26.885
He... help.

55:26.956 --> 55:28.515
Purna Shalabhasana!

55:28.591 --> 55:30.617
What? Full locust.

55:30.694 --> 55:32.526
Mom, what are you talking about?
Is he having a seizure?

55:32.595 --> 55:36.464
No, I think he's stretching.
Looks like Ashtanga yoga.

55:37.734 --> 55:41.728
There's the Shashankasana Pose.
Nice form, Joe.

55:43.106 --> 55:44.972
Garudasana.

55:46.810 --> 55:49.473
Ardha-Kurmasana.

55:50.814 --> 55:53.409
Ardha Matsyendrasana.

55:55.085 --> 56:00.615
Dandayamana Biebhakta
Paschimottanasana!

56:02.726 --> 56:05.457
Yeah, I don't know that one.

56:06.763 --> 56:07.958
J... Joe, Joe...

56:08.031 --> 56:11.695
Ow... oh, no!
My body shouldn't do this.

56:11.768 --> 56:15.102
He is a very fit, young man.

56:19.976 --> 56:23.413
And Shivassana to end,
what a display!

56:23.480 --> 56:26.609
It's also known
as the dead body pose.

56:27.817 --> 56:30.651
A little pre-meal stretch
is good for everyone.

56:30.720 --> 56:33.121
Come on, Henry.
Come on, Michelle.

56:33.189 --> 56:34.714
Gather round.

56:38.094 --> 56:40.029
Our troops are exhausted, sir.

56:40.096 --> 56:41.997
They need rest
and cannot continue.

56:42.065 --> 56:46.503
They liked what he did?
They think he's fit?

56:46.569 --> 56:49.505
We need him ruined!

56:49.572 --> 56:52.804
Do something, Sam. You must be
the hand of vengeance.

56:52.876 --> 56:54.037
Fine.

56:55.478 --> 56:57.845
All right, team, let's eat!

57:12.762 --> 57:14.754
This is not
one of my better days.

57:16.466 --> 57:18.662
Well done, my son.

57:18.735 --> 57:21.728
(GROANS)

57:21.805 --> 57:22.966
Let's go home.

57:23.039 --> 57:25.008
What makes you think
this is over?

57:25.074 --> 57:26.736
It's over for me.

57:26.810 --> 57:29.837
What I just did... wasn't right.

57:34.784 --> 57:36.514
I am so sorry, Mom.

57:36.586 --> 57:37.815
Don't worry about it.

57:37.887 --> 57:40.015
Everyone's okay
and that's what matters.

57:40.089 --> 57:41.990
Besides I haven't seen an
explosion like that...

57:42.058 --> 57:44.721
since I smuggled
antiquities out of Egypt.

57:44.794 --> 57:46.956
Yeah. Love you, Mom.

57:47.030 --> 57:50.523
Well, saves me some money
on a hair cut, at least.

57:50.600 --> 57:53.035
No hard feelings, Joe.
Hope your luck changes.

57:53.102 --> 57:55.970
Look, can I apologize for...

57:56.039 --> 57:58.634
Not right now, just drive.

58:02.178 --> 58:04.204
Hey, hey, Michelle, wait up!

58:04.280 --> 58:07.478
Look, I would really appreciate
it if you just left.

58:10.019 --> 58:13.478
Oh, man, this is gonna be great.

58:13.556 --> 58:14.683
Michelle.

58:14.757 --> 58:17.556
Joe, I'm working right now and
do not have the temperament.

58:17.627 --> 58:19.220
Please, let me explain.

58:19.295 --> 58:20.923
Explain what?

58:20.997 --> 58:25.492
That you ruined my parents' house with
some outlandish yoga-infused craziness?

58:25.568 --> 58:26.627
No, I...

58:26.703 --> 58:29.673
Look, I have seen klutzy before and
I thought that was adorable...

58:29.739 --> 58:32.231
but today's events,
that was too far.

58:32.308 --> 58:33.936
What is wrong with you?

58:34.010 --> 58:37.742
If I tell you, you promise
not to think I'm crazy?

58:37.814 --> 58:39.612
Go ahead, I'm listening.

58:39.682 --> 58:41.275
Pixies. Pixies?

58:41.551 --> 58:45.579
Pixies... it's this whole
curse thing.

58:45.655 --> 58:46.679
It started a while ago.

58:46.756 --> 58:47.756
You think that's funny?

58:47.824 --> 58:48.985
What? Hah!

58:49.058 --> 58:52.756
You think you can win me over by
blaming Pixies for your problems?

58:52.829 --> 58:54.957
No, it's the truth,
absolute truth!

58:55.031 --> 58:56.727
Joe, just go home...

58:56.799 --> 58:58.893
before you break something
I won't forgive you for.

59:02.705 --> 59:03.934
There! Behind you!

59:04.007 --> 59:06.704
Stop! I don't have the
patience for this any more.

59:06.776 --> 59:09.075
I got it!

59:15.184 --> 59:17.551
Please leave, Joe.

59:17.620 --> 59:19.748
I...

59:19.822 --> 59:23.054
I'm... I'm so sorry.

59:23.126 --> 59:26.324
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

59:29.699 --> 59:30.997
What next?

59:31.067 --> 59:32.126
Sam?

59:32.201 --> 59:33.863
We go home.

59:33.937 --> 59:35.235
This is over.

59:35.305 --> 59:36.603
Huh?

59:36.673 --> 59:38.801
You're not thinking big enough,
Sammy boy.

59:38.875 --> 59:42.039
<i>(MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

59:43.379 --> 59:46.315
Joe? You okay?

59:46.382 --> 59:48.044
Joe!

59:53.356 --> 59:56.690
About time... gimme a hand.

59:56.759 --> 59:58.990
Perfect! Oh, no.

01:00:02.065 --> 01:00:03.124
Ugh...

01:00:21.150 --> 01:00:23.381
Oh, this is the best day
of my life.

01:00:28.324 --> 01:00:31.294
<i>(MUSIC CHANGES)</i>

01:00:32.795 --> 01:00:35.697
Dad, this is really
going too far.

01:00:35.765 --> 01:00:38.064
All is fair in war and love.

01:00:42.972 --> 01:00:44.736
Dad... Son...

01:00:44.807 --> 01:00:48.869
well-placed tree sap
can work wonders.

01:00:48.945 --> 01:00:50.243
Dad, look at him.

01:00:50.313 --> 01:00:54.648
All I see is a big load
of human scum.

01:01:16.372 --> 01:01:18.034
Hello?

01:01:19.142 --> 01:01:20.872
Joe, are you okay?

01:01:22.278 --> 01:01:25.043
How could you possibly think
this is right, Dad?

01:01:25.114 --> 01:01:29.051
Right or wrong,
we did what must be done.

01:01:29.118 --> 01:01:32.020
Pixies, our war is over!

01:01:32.088 --> 01:01:35.183
And history shall declare
us victorious.

01:01:37.460 --> 01:01:39.326
( MOANS)

01:01:44.867 --> 01:01:46.358
(WHINES)

01:01:49.005 --> 01:01:52.305
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

01:02:11.260 --> 01:02:13.286
I need a status update.

01:02:13.362 --> 01:02:17.356
Sir, it looks like this is gonna
take a lot longer than we expected.

01:02:17.433 --> 01:02:18.958
How long are we talking?

01:02:19.035 --> 01:02:20.901
Well, if you factor in...

01:02:20.970 --> 01:02:21.970
I said how long!

01:02:22.038 --> 01:02:24.803
A few dozen years.

01:02:24.874 --> 01:02:26.172
What are our options?

01:02:26.242 --> 01:02:29.144
We could send half of our Pixies
to join another colony.

01:02:29.212 --> 01:02:32.239
Send scouts to check for room
in allied villages.

01:02:32.315 --> 01:02:34.784
Start dividing us up
into refugee camps.

01:02:34.851 --> 01:02:36.843
Yes, sir, will do.

01:02:37.954 --> 01:02:39.923
So much for our kingdom.

01:02:42.125 --> 01:02:44.219
What are we gonna do?

01:02:44.293 --> 01:02:45.886
I have an idea.

01:02:50.366 --> 01:02:55.031
Oh, wow, you've really
let this place go...

01:02:55.104 --> 01:02:56.436
and yourself.

01:02:56.506 --> 01:02:59.032
Have you not moved at all?

01:03:00.881 --> 01:03:02.521
We're gonna need
to get you in the shower.

01:03:02.545 --> 01:03:05.913
Why, so you can trip me again?
Set my room on fire?

01:03:05.982 --> 01:03:07.109
Continue to ruin my life?

01:03:07.183 --> 01:03:08.811
No, no, I never...

01:03:08.885 --> 01:03:10.945
Look, I didn't want to do it.

01:03:11.020 --> 01:03:14.320
This was all because of my brother,
and he would have hated this.

01:03:14.390 --> 01:03:17.827
He always used to tell me to treat
people how you want to be treated.

01:03:19.395 --> 01:03:21.955
Do onto others. Huh?

01:03:22.031 --> 01:03:26.469
We humans have a saying, "Do onto
others as you want done onto you."

01:03:26.536 --> 01:03:28.528
That sounds like my brother.

01:03:28.604 --> 01:03:31.540
My mom used to say it.
It's why I gave up.

01:03:31.607 --> 01:03:34.133
I deserved your punishment.

01:03:34.210 --> 01:03:37.510
I think we deserved the same, after
ruining your life for so long.

01:03:38.080 --> 01:03:39.241
So now what?

01:03:39.315 --> 01:03:41.341
Now we're gonna stop this
horrible cycle...

01:03:41.417 --> 01:03:44.546
and we're gonna do
something good... together.

01:03:44.620 --> 01:03:46.987
I like the idea, but how?

01:03:47.056 --> 01:03:49.082
First, you're gonna
have a shower...

01:03:49.158 --> 01:03:51.286
and next, I'm gonna
burn that chair.

01:03:51.360 --> 01:03:52.555
Good call.

01:03:58.134 --> 01:04:00.160
It does feel good
to build something.

01:04:00.236 --> 01:04:02.603
Pixies are not great builders.

01:04:02.872 --> 01:04:05.000
Magnificent tricksters,
fantastic ruiners...

01:04:05.074 --> 01:04:09.512
great smashers, but after we break something,
we never have to put it back together.

01:04:09.579 --> 01:04:12.048
We really suck
at building things.

01:04:12.114 --> 01:04:15.016
Really? Birds build nests out of
sticks in like a day.

01:04:15.084 --> 01:04:18.111
Birds eat us. Touché.

01:04:20.389 --> 01:04:21.914
Let's keep the chatter down.

01:04:21.991 --> 01:04:24.192
No one else can see me and
people are starting to stare.

01:04:30.433 --> 01:04:32.163
Are you invisible?

01:04:32.235 --> 01:04:34.534
No, we're wings and blood,
just like you, Joe.

01:04:34.604 --> 01:04:35.970
Don't over think it, big guy.

01:04:36.038 --> 01:04:38.439
Hey, believe me, most things
in life, I don't over think.

01:04:38.507 --> 01:04:41.477
This time, though, I have
put some thought into this.

01:04:51.487 --> 01:04:54.355
You're Samuel's friend Twitch,
aren't you?

01:04:54.423 --> 01:04:57.518
This is where I get my medal
for brilliant combat strategy.

01:04:57.593 --> 01:05:00.062
Have you seen my son, Samuel?

01:05:00.129 --> 01:05:01.893
What? No medal?

01:05:01.964 --> 01:05:04.297
I, um... saw him.

01:05:04.367 --> 01:05:06.393
Well, do you know
where he is now?

01:05:06.469 --> 01:05:08.165
I think so.

01:05:08.237 --> 01:05:13.301
Well, I'd like to, er... um...
apologize for my behavior.

01:05:13.376 --> 01:05:16.505
He may have been a little wiser
than I gave him credit for.

01:05:16.579 --> 01:05:19.481
We'll find him, sir!

01:05:19.548 --> 01:05:21.517
Come on, Twitch.

01:05:21.584 --> 01:05:24.679
Since when have you been
the leading type?

01:05:30.259 --> 01:05:31.659
Hurry up, Chunky.

01:05:31.727 --> 01:05:35.596
Listen, just because I might not
be what you call a small pixie...

01:05:35.665 --> 01:05:38.032
doesn't mean you can pick on me.

01:05:38.100 --> 01:05:40.695
I can't look like the Pixies
in those magazines.

01:05:40.970 --> 01:05:42.563
I'm sorry, Max.

01:05:42.638 --> 01:05:44.630
( LAUGHING)

01:05:44.707 --> 01:05:46.699
He's torturing Sammy.

01:05:46.976 --> 01:05:49.536
( LAUGHING CONTINUES)
It sounds like laughter to me.

01:05:49.612 --> 01:05:52.104
Of course, it sounds
like laughter!

01:05:52.181 --> 01:05:54.173
It's diabolical laughter!

01:05:54.250 --> 01:05:57.687
Let him go, you mad man!
Let him go!

01:05:57.753 --> 01:05:59.949
Let's go tell the king.

01:06:04.293 --> 01:06:07.263
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

01:06:18.174 --> 01:06:21.667
Oh, great majesty,
lord of all we survey...

01:06:21.744 --> 01:06:23.542
he who is higher
than the holiest of...

01:06:23.612 --> 01:06:26.138
Okay, okay, just get to it.

01:06:26.215 --> 01:06:31.552
Your son, our friend, the prince Samuel, is
being tortured by that big-headed human.

01:06:31.620 --> 01:06:33.714
What? Is this true?

01:06:33.789 --> 01:06:36.759
It is true, his head is massive.

01:06:37.026 --> 01:06:40.019
He's pulling Sam apart,
wing by wing!

01:06:40.096 --> 01:06:43.157
You two, enough already,
round up the troops.

01:06:43.232 --> 01:06:45.463
We have one last battle
to fight.

01:06:45.534 --> 01:06:48.504
Ah, what's with all the fuss?

01:06:48.571 --> 01:06:50.335
Samuel! My boy!

01:06:50.406 --> 01:06:52.637
You're alive!

01:06:52.708 --> 01:06:55.007
Did that... that human hurt you?

01:06:55.077 --> 01:06:58.172
I've been working with Joe.

01:06:58.247 --> 01:06:59.647
He wants to help us and...

01:06:59.715 --> 01:07:01.741
Help us? But he hates us...

01:07:01.817 --> 01:07:04.116
just as we hate him.

01:07:04.186 --> 01:07:08.317
Joe doesn't hate us, he was
angry, but we ruined his life.

01:07:08.391 --> 01:07:11.020
You were angry
because William was hurt.

01:07:11.093 --> 01:07:14.495
Both of us are allowed to be angry,
but what we did when we were angry...

01:07:14.563 --> 01:07:18.432
it was wrong, Dad,
we were both wrong.

01:07:18.501 --> 01:07:21.232
You have an entire kingdom to lead
and you're going to lose them.

01:07:21.303 --> 01:07:25.570
Let it go, Dad.
Let's stop the fighting.

01:07:25.641 --> 01:07:29.408
Forgive me, sir, you've been
so worried over William...

01:07:29.478 --> 01:07:31.606
you forgot about Sam.

01:07:31.680 --> 01:07:35.447
He's a great son,
and an amazing leader.

01:07:35.518 --> 01:07:36.747
Huh.

01:07:36.819 --> 01:07:39.687
I can help lead our people
in a new direction...

01:07:39.755 --> 01:07:41.553
but I need you to trust me.

01:07:41.624 --> 01:07:45.618
Look at you... Samuel, oh, oh...

01:07:51.534 --> 01:07:54.834
I am sorry, my son. I'm sorry.

01:07:56.572 --> 01:07:57.699
Follow me, Dad.

01:07:57.773 --> 01:07:59.139
I have a surprise to show you.

01:07:59.208 --> 01:08:02.269
I have a surprise for everyone!

01:08:03.546 --> 01:08:06.778
Everyone, this is Joe.

01:08:06.849 --> 01:08:09.182
PIXIES Hi, Joe!

01:08:09.251 --> 01:08:10.810
Hi.

01:08:10.886 --> 01:08:14.789
I... I'm really sorry about
what I did to your village.

01:08:14.857 --> 01:08:16.553
I lost my temper.

01:08:16.625 --> 01:08:21.723
What I did was wrong and
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

01:08:23.532 --> 01:08:27.627
And William, I wish
I could take it all back.

01:08:27.703 --> 01:08:30.194
Sam told me something that
William used to tell him...

01:08:30.272 --> 01:08:33.174
something my own family
once said.

01:08:33.242 --> 01:08:35.676
Do onto others as you'd
have done onto you.

01:08:35.743 --> 01:08:39.408
I hope what I'm about to show you repays
just some of the damage I've caused you.

01:08:41.550 --> 01:08:43.451
Welcome to your new home.

01:08:43.519 --> 01:08:46.113
Each house has plumbing
and electricity.

01:08:46.188 --> 01:08:48.783
Sammy mentioned that sometimes the
elements can be harsh out there...

01:08:48.858 --> 01:08:50.850
and this thing is storm-proof.

01:08:50.926 --> 01:08:54.225
I can attach it easily to the
rest, assuming you want it...

01:08:54.296 --> 01:08:56.457
and we can both forgive
each other.

01:08:56.532 --> 01:09:02.403
Joe, um, we forgive you,
and we are also sorry.

01:09:02.470 --> 01:09:05.635
I know this is what William
would have wanted.

01:09:05.707 --> 01:09:07.267
It is, Dad.

01:09:07.343 --> 01:09:08.834
William! My son!

01:09:08.911 --> 01:09:10.573
You're okay!

01:09:10.645 --> 01:09:13.774
Ooh, careful, guys, yeah,
still not quite healed yet.

01:09:13.849 --> 01:09:16.580
William, I'm so sorry!

01:09:16.652 --> 01:09:18.814
It was never my intention...

01:09:18.888 --> 01:09:21.448
I'm really glad you're okay.

01:09:21.524 --> 01:09:24.426
Pixies may be small,
but we're feisty.

01:09:24.493 --> 01:09:25.688
So, I've learned.

01:09:25.761 --> 01:09:29.663
Well, Joe, I've been wrong
all along.

01:09:29.732 --> 01:09:34.170
It seems we can co-exist...
and peacefully.

01:09:34.236 --> 01:09:35.932
Way to go, Dad!

01:09:36.205 --> 01:09:39.265
Dad, William, with everything
Joe's done for us...

01:09:39.341 --> 01:09:41.435
maybe there's something
we can do for him.

01:09:44.647 --> 01:09:47.481
Mrs. Mayor, you look
absolutely stunning.

01:09:47.550 --> 01:09:48.848
Just stunning!

01:09:48.917 --> 01:09:51.546
Deanna, you must give me
a call sometime next week.

01:09:51.620 --> 01:09:54.351
We need to talk TV interviews
for Michelle.

01:09:54.423 --> 01:09:58.451
You have my card? Get it off
the desk inside! Ciao!

01:09:59.228 --> 01:10:02.221
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:10:04.366 --> 01:10:07.859
How's my brilliant artist doing,
on her big night?

01:10:07.937 --> 01:10:09.269
Terrible.

01:10:09.338 --> 01:10:12.308
Michelle, honey, I know
you've had setbacks...

01:10:12.374 --> 01:10:14.809
but we couldn't push this
opening off any longer.

01:10:14.877 --> 01:10:17.711
Use the ones you've repaired
and let's hit it!

01:10:17.780 --> 01:10:19.874
Barbara, they look terrible.

01:10:19.949 --> 01:10:22.282
I can't represent myself
like this.

01:10:22.351 --> 01:10:28.450
Michelle, my dear, you're established,
respected, published and never rejected.

01:10:28.524 --> 01:10:32.552
In the art world, that means
your mistakes are art.

01:10:32.628 --> 01:10:34.460
And everyone will love you
for it.

01:10:34.530 --> 01:10:36.294
Just say it's part
of the exhibit.

01:10:36.365 --> 01:10:38.960
You can say it represents
the broken world we live in.

01:10:39.835 --> 01:10:42.532
Are you sure?
I... oh, I don't know.

01:10:42.605 --> 01:10:44.904
I've been doing this
for a long time, honey.

01:10:44.974 --> 01:10:48.342
Now you've got 300 people who
don't give a rat about the truth.

01:10:48.410 --> 01:10:50.743
They just want to see some art.

01:10:52.548 --> 01:10:55.382
[BARBARA] Ladies and gentlemen,
attention, please! Oh...

01:10:55.451 --> 01:10:57.682
Now, without any further
adieu...

01:10:57.753 --> 01:11:02.851
let me introduce the lady of the
evening, Miss Michelle Myers.

01:11:02.925 --> 01:11:04.894
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)
Oh, thank you.

01:11:04.960 --> 01:11:06.952
Oh... oh my, thank you.

01:11:07.029 --> 01:11:09.624
That is just so nice,
thank you so much.

01:11:09.698 --> 01:11:13.658
Well, firstly, I wanted to start
by thanking all of you...

01:11:13.736 --> 01:11:15.432
as my manager Barbara
just did...

01:11:15.504 --> 01:11:20.374
for your understanding in regards
to this ever-changing opening day.

01:11:20.442 --> 01:11:22.604
This project has been
a long time coming...

01:11:22.678 --> 01:11:26.672
and just as I thought I'd reached
the end of this long journey...

01:11:26.749 --> 01:11:32.017
fate or circumstance caused some havoc in my
personal life that effected my work here.

01:11:34.857 --> 01:11:38.316
Um, I am missing some of the
little people for...

01:11:38.394 --> 01:11:39.862
(CLEARS THROAT) Excuse me.

01:11:39.928 --> 01:11:42.796
Uh, hi, hello,
sorry to interrupt.

01:11:42.865 --> 01:11:45.494
Excuse me. Joe...

01:11:45.567 --> 01:11:49.561
Special delivery for a Michelle.
Where should I put it?

01:11:49.638 --> 01:11:51.539
Joe, if you so much as...

01:11:51.607 --> 01:11:52.870
Trust me.

01:11:52.941 --> 01:11:57.777
Um, ladies and gentlemen, it appears that
I do have another guest for my carnival.

01:11:57.846 --> 01:12:00.543
Looks like he arrived on-time,
after all.

01:12:05.020 --> 01:12:06.682
Trust me, please.

01:12:11.460 --> 01:12:14.089
Okay, you're all set.

01:12:14.363 --> 01:12:17.333
<i>(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

01:12:31.980 --> 01:12:35.815
This is unbelievable!
This is going to go viral!

01:12:35.884 --> 01:12:39.787
No, better, this is going
to go antibiotic!

01:12:39.855 --> 01:12:41.949
I feel healthier
just watching it.

01:12:42.024 --> 01:12:43.356
Wow.

01:12:43.425 --> 01:12:45.985
And the delivery guy
was a great touch.

01:12:46.061 --> 01:12:48.895
So avent garde,
what showmanship!

01:12:48.964 --> 01:12:51.024
Oh, thank you.

01:12:51.100 --> 01:12:53.569
They look so real!

01:12:53.635 --> 01:12:55.934
You must have spent a fortune
on these little robots!

01:13:05.180 --> 01:13:09.811
This is...

01:13:09.885 --> 01:13:11.547
I can't believe it.

01:13:11.620 --> 01:13:14.488
I'm not looking for an apology, I
wouldn't have believed me, either.

01:13:14.556 --> 01:13:17.583
I just didn't want you to think
I was making fun of you.

01:13:17.659 --> 01:13:18.957
I'll never do that.

01:13:19.027 --> 01:13:21.019
And I couldn't show you they're
real, because...

01:13:21.096 --> 01:13:23.088
Because we don't exist.

01:13:23.165 --> 01:13:26.465
This is a one-time favor
we owed Joe, okay?

01:13:26.535 --> 01:13:28.163
Wh... yeah, I understand.

01:13:29.838 --> 01:13:31.636
It's a really long story.

01:13:31.707 --> 01:13:33.107
Are you still mad at me?

01:13:35.210 --> 01:13:38.078
Look at that.
He got the girl, after all.

01:13:38.147 --> 01:13:40.514
She is pretty cute...

01:13:40.582 --> 01:13:42.414
for a creature without wings.

01:13:42.484 --> 01:13:44.646
I don't see you with a girl.

01:13:44.720 --> 01:13:46.552
I don't see you with one,
either.

01:13:46.622 --> 01:13:50.684
Yeah, well, I've got you
to keep me company, right?

01:13:50.759 --> 01:13:52.421
Always.

